  "prompt_text": "Within the first 1.20 seconds, one brief forearm impact makes the white-haired warrior's upper body recoil and the rear foot make exactly one short backward recovery placement, then the receiver stabilizes. The black-armored warrior starts already close but not touching, shifts forward from the legs and shoulder along a chest-height force line, and strikes the white-haired warrior's upper torso with one compact forearm contact. Only after contact do the receiver's chest and shoulders move backward; the front foot supports while the rear foot makes the single short backward recovery placement. Contact is readable by 0.50 seconds, the recoil follows immediately after contact, the step completes by 1.20 seconds, and the stable result is readable by 1.50 seconds. The impact ends immediately after contact and the attacker retracts instead of maintaining pressure. After stabilization, preserve subtle living motion rather than a frozen pose. Cinematic fantasy in a rainy ancient temple courtyard with a wet stone floor, one continuous medium eye-level static shot, preserving both identities and readable screen direction. No reaction before contact, prolonged push, repeated hit, multiple steps, sliding, flight, fall, wall collision, extra subject, magic, injury, gore, camera movement, or scene change.",
